'''Igor Thiago Nascimento Rodrigues''' (born 26 June 2001), known simply as '''Igor Thiago''' ({{IPA|pt-BR|ˈiɡoʁ tʃiˈaɡu}})​, is a Brazilian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[striker (association football)|striker]] for {{English football updater|Brentfor}} club [[Brentford F.C.|Brentford]] and the [[Brazil national football team|Brazil national team]].

==Early life==
Igor Thiago was born in Gama, Federal District, and was 13 years old when he lost his father, and supported his street-cleaner mother María Diva by working in construction as a bricklayer, odd-jobbing at fairs, and by handing out flyers.<ref>{{cite news |date=30 August 2023 |title=Igor Thiago, la primera venta de Ronaldo en Cruzeiro, destaca en el rival de Osasuna en la Conference |url=https://www.marca.com/futbol/conference-league/2023/08/30/64eee5efca4741bf608b457c.html |access-date=16 February 2024 |website=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]] |language=Spanish}}</ref><ref name="bbc.com">{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/ce9r4g2yvmko|title=Igor Thiago: Brentford striker is making up for lost time after scoring two against Manchester United|date=27 September 2025|website=BBC Sport}}</ref>

He did not consider a career in football, but began playing at Gremio Ocidental, where his brother was already a player. He started playing [[futsal]] and had trials at several teams before joining the under-17 team of Verê, from the interior of Paraná, when he was sixteen. He later joined [[Cruzeiro Esporte Clube|Cruzeiro]]'s academy in 2019.<ref name="Sky">{{cite news|title=Igor Thiago: Who is the Club Brugge striker heading to the Premier League as Brentford's possible Ivan Toney replacement?|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11748/13072079/igor-thiago-who-is-the-club-brugge-striker-heading-to-the-premier-league-as-brentfords-possible-ivan-toney-replacement|website=[[Sky Sports]]|date=15 February 2024|accessdate=16 February 2024}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Harris |first=Jay |date=2024-03-01 |title=Who is Igor Thiago? How long have Brentford tracked him? Is he Ivan Toney's replacement? |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5307744/2024/03/01/igor-thiago-brentford/ |access-date=2025-12-01 |work=The New York Times |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Cruzeiro===
On 22 January 2020, Thiago made his professional debut as an 18-year-old when he started for Cruzeiro in their [[Campeonato Mineiro]] match against [[Boa Esporte Clube|Boa Esporte]].<ref name="Cruzeiro vs. Boa 2 - 0">{{cite web |title=Cruzeiro vs. Boa 2 – 0 |url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2020/01/23/brazil/mineiro-1/cruzeiro-esporte-clube-belo-horizonte/ituiutaba-esporte-clube/3193206/ |website=Soccerway |accessdate=25 January 2020 |archive-date=11 February 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210211072158/https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2020/01/23/brazil/mineiro-1/cruzeiro-esporte-clube-belo-horizonte/ituiutaba-esporte-clube/3193206/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

During his three years with the club, Thiago scored 10 goals in 64 appearances.<ref>{{cite news |date=29 August 2023 |title=Ex-Cruzeiro, Thiago superou infância difícil e hoje brilha na Europa |trans-title=Former Cruzeiro player Thiago overcame a difficult childhood and now shines in Europe |url=https://trivela.com.br/europa/thiago-brugge-cruzeiro/ |access-date=16 February 2024 |website=Trivela |language=Portuguese}}</ref>

===Ludogorets Razgrad===
[[File:Igor Thiago, Ludogorets Razgrad footballer.jpg|thumb|140px|left|Igor Thiago with [[PFC Ludogorets Razgrad|Ludogorets Razgrad]] in 2022]]

After a series of rumours, on 2 March 2022, Thiago finally signed with the Bulgarian champions [[PFC Ludogorets Razgrad|Ludogorets Razgrad]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Тиаго и Групер: Идваме в голям клуб |url=https://www.ludogorets.com/bg/news/?i=4704 |publisher=PFC Ludogorets Razgrad |language=Bulgarian |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230415230512/https://www.ludogorets.com/bg/news/?i=4704 |archive-date=15 April 2023 |access-date=30 April 2022}}</ref> He joined [[PFC Ludogorets Razgrad II|Ludogorets II]] in order to adapt to the Bulgarian league and made his debut on 18 April in a league match against [[PFC Litex Lovech|Litex Lovech]], scoring his first goal.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Лудогорец II загуби с 1:2 от Литекс (Ловеч) |url=https://ludogorets.com/bg/news/?i=4798 |publisher=PFC Ludogorets Razgrad |language=Bulgarian |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230415230512/https://ludogorets.com/bg/news/?i=4798 |archive-date=15 April 2023 |access-date=30 April 2022}}</ref> A week later, he scored a brace in a 3–2 away defeat against [[FC Dobrudzha Dobrich|Dobrudzha Dobrich]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Два гола на нов не спомогнаха на Лудогорец 2, Добруджа с витален успех |url=https://gong.bg/bg-football/vtora-liga/multimedia/video/dva-gola-na-nov-ne-spomognaha-na-ludogorec-2-dobrudzha-s-vitalen-uspeh-679661 |website=Gong.bg |language=Bulgarian |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220430222604/https://gong.bg/bg-football/vtora-liga/multimedia/video/dva-gola-na-nov-ne-spomognaha-na-ludogorec-2-dobrudzha-s-vitalen-uspeh-679661 |archive-date=30 April 2022 |access-date=30 April 2022}}</ref>

Thiago's good start for the second team granted him a call-up to the first team where he made his debut in a league match against [[PFC CSKA Sofia|CSKA Sofia]], coming on as a substitute and marking his debut for the first team with a goal.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Лудогорец с шампионска победа над ЦСКА-София |url=https://ludogorets.com/bg/news/?i=4818 |publisher=PFC Ludogorets Razgrad |language=Bulgarian |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220430222605/https://ludogorets.com/bg/news/?i=4818 |archive-date=30 April 2022 |access-date=30 April 2022}}</ref>

With Ludogorets, Thiago won back-to-back [[First Professional Football League (Bulgaria)|Bulgarian First League]] titles for [[2021–22 First Professional Football League (Bulgaria)|2021–22]] and [[2022–23 First Professional Football League (Bulgaria)|2022–23]], as well as the [[2022–23 Bulgarian Cup|2023 Bulgarian Cup]] and [[2022 Bulgarian Supercup]], contributing to the club's success with 21 goals in 55 games.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Ludogorets realized a record transfer in Bulgaria |url=https://www.ludogorets.com/en/news/?i=5539 |publisher=PFC Ludogorets Razgrad |language=Bulgarian  |date=12 June 2023}}</ref>

===Club Brugge===
On 12 June 2023, Thiago signed for [[Belgian Pro League]] club [[Club Brugge KV|Club Brugge]] on a four-year contract.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.clubbrugge.be/en/news/igor-thiago-moves-to-club-brugge |title=Igor Thiago moves to Club Brugge |publisher=Club Brugge KV |date=12 June 2023 |access-date=12 June 2023|archive-date=12 June 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230612161316/https://www.clubbrugge.be/en/news/igor-thiago-moves-to-club-brugge|url-status=live}}</ref> The €7.9&nbsp;million fee received by Ludogorets was a record for a Bulgarian club.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ludogorets.com/bg/news/?i=5539 |title=Лудогорец реализира рекорден трансфер |publisher=PFC Ludogorets Razgrad |language=Bulgarian |date=12 June 2023 |access-date=12 June 2023 |archive-date=12 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230612161316/https://www.ludogorets.com/bg/news/?i=5539 |url-status=live}}</ref>

Having started in a 3–0 win over [[Aarhus Gymnastikforening|Aarhus]] in the [[2023-24 UEFA Conference League|UEFA Conference League]] qualifiers on 27 July 2023, Thiago scored in his first two league games for Club Brugge, a late equaliser to earn a 1–1 draw against [[KV Mechelen|Mechelen]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://sporza.be/nl/matches/voetbal/jupiler-pro-league/2023-2024/regulier/01/club-brugge-kv-mechelen-club-brugge-laat-meteen-punten-liggen-tegen-kv-mechelen-dat-vloekt-op-de-var-en-1-2-laat-liggen~1687437247220/|title=Club Brugge laat meteen punten liggen tegen KV Mechelen, dat vloekt op de VAR én 1–2 laat liggen (Club Brugge immediately drops points against KV Mechelen, who criticise VAR and misses 2–1 win)|work=Sporza|date=30 July 2023|access-date=16 February 2024|language=nl}}</ref> then netting the only goal in a 1–0 win at [[K.V.C. Westerlo|Westerlo]] to put the club near the top of the table early in the season.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://sporza.be/nl/matches/voetbal/jupiler-pro-league/2023-2024/regulier/02/westerlo-club-brugge-dominant-club-brugge-bibbert-in-slot-naar-eerste-seizoenszege-op-bezoek-bij-westerlo~1687437129209/|title=Dominant Club Brugge bibbert in slot naar eerste seizoenszege op bezoek bij Westerlo (Dominant Club Brugge finally staggers towards its first victory of season at Westerlo)|work=Sporza|date=6 August 2023|access-date=16 February 2024|language=nl}}</ref>

Scoring the opening goal in a 4–2 win over [[Royal Charleroi S.C.|Charleroi]] on 16 September 2023 saw him reach six goals in all competitions,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://sporza.be/nl/matches/voetbal/jupiler-pro-league/2023-2024/regulier/07/club-brugge-charleroi-wonderboy-antonio-nusa-schenkt-club-brugge-ultiem-de-overwinning-na-kat-en-muisspelletje-met-charleroi~1687438026216/|title=Wonderboy Antonio Nusa schenkt Club Brugge ultiem de overwinning na kat-en-muisspelletje met Charleroi (Wonderboy Antonio Nusa gives Club Brugge ultimate victory after cat-and-mouse game with Charleroi)|work=Sporza|date=16 September 2023|access-date=16 February 2024|language=nl}}</ref> but Thiago didn't score in Club's next nine games, finally breaking his duck in a 6–0 [[Belgian Cup]] victory at [[K Beerschot VA|Beerschot]] on 1 November.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://sporza.be/nl/matches/voetbal/croky-cup/2023-2024/1-16-finale/01/beerschot-club-brugge-club-brugge-bezorgt-het-kiel-een-horroravond-en-smeert-beerschot-een-0-6-pandoering-aan~1694507283752/|title=Club Brugge bezorgt het Kiel een horroravond en smeert Beerschot een 0-6-pandoering aan (Club Brugge gives Kiel a horror evening and Beerschot a 6–0 pounding)|work=Sporza|date=1 November 2023|access-date=16 February 2024|language=nl}}</ref> However, there were no more league goals until December of that year.

He netted a double in a 5–0 away win over [[Beşiktaş J.K.|Beşiktaş]] in the Conference League which sparked a major goalscoring run from the Brazilian striker,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://sporza.be/nl/matches/voetbal/eur/uefa-europa-conference-league/2023-2024/groep-d/05/besiktas-club-brugge-club-brugge-speelt-een-absolute-referentiematch-en-smeert-besiktas-forfaitscore-aan~1687444083796/|title=Club Brugge speelt een absolute referentiematch en smeert Besiktas forfaitscore aan (A milestone match for Club Brugge, beating Besiktas by a forfeit score)|work=Sporza|date=30 November 2023|access-date=16 February 2024|language=nl}}</ref> going on to fire 18 goals in his next 12 games across December 2023 and January 2024. Thiago was only shut out in one of those matches, against Mechelen where a header he scored was erroneously ruled out for offside.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://sporza.be/nl/matches/voetbal/jupiler-pro-league/2023-2024/regulier/17/kv-mechelen-club-brugge-zegereeks-club-brugge-wordt-afgebroken-door-stug-kv-mechelen~1687437549890/|title=Zegereeks Club Brugge wordt afgebroken door stug KV Mechelen (Club Brugge's winning streak is interrupted by tough KV Mechelen)|work=Sporza|date=10 December 2023|access-date=16 February 2024|language=nl}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.hln.be/club-brugge/kijk-match-wordt-niet-herspeeld-referee-department-licht-blunder-bij-goal-thiago-toe-van-damme-voorlopig-geen-var-meer~adb83679/|title=KIJK. "Match wordt niet herspeeld": Referee Department licht blunder bij goal Thiago toe, Van Damme voorlopig geen VAR meer (WATCH. "Match will not be replayed": Referee Department explains blunder at Thiago goal, Van Damme no longer VAR for the time being)|work=[[Het Laatste Nieuws]]|date=11 December 2023|access-date=16 February 2024|language=nl}}</ref> After that blank, Thiago scored in his next eight games.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://sporza.be/nl/2024/01/22/plots-is-de-twijfelspits-de-strafste-van-europa-hoe-valt-de-transformatie-van-igor-thiago-te-verklaren~1705938768034/|title=Plots is de twijfelspits de strafste van Europa: hoe valt de transformatie van Igor Thiago te verklaren? (Suddenly the peak of doubt is the strongest in Europe: how can Igor Thiago's transformation be explained?)|work=Sporza|date=23 January 2024|access-date=16 February 2024|language=nl}}</ref>

===Brentford===
[[File:Igor Thiago and Mathias Jensen 27122025 (1).jpg|thumb|225px|Igor Thiago with Brentford in 2025]]

On 14 February 2024, [[Premier League]] club [[Brentford F.C.|Brentford]] announced an agreement for the signing of Thiago on a five-year deal, which would come into effect on 1 July.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.brentfordfc.com/en/news/article/first-team-igor-thiago-club-brugge-brentford-transfer- |title=Brentford Sign Forward Igor Thiago |publisher=Brentford FC |date=14 February 2024 |access-date=14 February 2024}}</ref> The fee was undisclosed by the club, but reported to be in the region of a club-record £30&nbsp;million.<ref>{{cite news |date=14 February 2024 |title=Brentford announce £30m signing of Club Brugge striker Igor Thiago |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2024/feb/14/brentford-announce-30m-signing-of-club-brugge-striker-igor-thiago |access-date=15 February 2024 |work=The Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref> In Belgian terms, this was a new Pro League record sale of €38&nbsp;million.<ref>{{Cite news |date=15 February 2024 |title=Het verhaal achter de (stiekeme) recordtransfer van Igor Thiago: "Zelfs Fabrizio Romano wist dit niet" |trans-title=The story behind Igor Thiago's (secret) record transfer: "Even Fabrizio Romano didn't know this" |url=https://sporza.be/nl/2024/02/15/het-verhaal-achter-de-stiekeme-recordtransfer-van-igor-thiago-zelfs-fabrizio-romano-wist-dit-niet~1708000273413/ |access-date=16 February 2024 |work=Sporza |language=nl}}</ref>

On 20 July 2024, Thiago suffered a [[Meniscus tear|meniscus injury]] on his Brentford debut in a pre-season friendly, and was subsequently expected to be out of action for the remainder of the year.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/c87rzgln4p8o |title=
Brentford signing Thiago out until end of year |website=BBC Sport |date=31 July 2024 |access-date=31 July 2024}}</ref> However, on 23 November, Thiago made his first appearance for the club against [[Everton F.C.|Everton]], when he replaced [[Yoane Wissa]] in the 72nd minute.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Hafez |first1=Shamoon |title=Everton 0–0 Brentford: Toffees held to goalless draw by 10-man visitors |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c8jyve474r3t |access-date=3 January 2025 |work=BBC Sport |date=23 November 2024}}</ref> Despite the brief return, he missed most of the remainder of the [[2024–25 Premier League|2024–25 season]], only making his return on 4 May 2025 in Brentford's 4–3 home victory against [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] in the league.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.brentfordfc.com/en/news/article/first-team-aaron-hickey-igor-thiago-injury-update-ipswich-town-v-brentford-premier-league |title='He will not start': Frank provides injury update before Brentford's trip to Ipswich |publisher=Brentford F.C. |date=8 May 2025 |access-date=18 August 2025}}</ref>

On 17 August 2025, Thiago scored his first goal for Brentford in a 3–1 away defeat against [[Nottingham Forest F.C.|Nottingham Forest]] in the club's opening game of the [[2025–26 Premier League|2025–26 season]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.brentfordfc.com/en/news/article/match-reports-nottingham-forest-3-brentford-1-premier-league |title=Nottingham Forest 3 Brentford 1: Thiago on target in opening day defeat |publisher=Brentford F.C. |date=17 August 2025 |access-date=18 August 2025}}</ref> On 27 September, Thiago scored a first half double in a 3–1 victory against Manchester United.<ref name="bbc.com"/> In November that year, he won the Premier League Player of the Month after, having scored five goals in four matches for his club.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.brentfordfc.com/en/news/article/first-team-igor-thiago-wins-premier-league-player-of-the-month-november-2025 |title=Thiago wins Premier League Player of the Month |publisher=Brentford F.C. |date=12 December 2025 }}</ref>

He scored his first hat-trick for the ''Bees'' in a 4–2 away win at Everton on 4 January 2026.<ref>{{Cite web|url= https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c5y23mym183t|title= Everton 2–4 Brentford: Igor Thiago hat-trick helps the Bees ease past the hosts|last=Rajan|first=Adwaidh|website=BBC Sport|date=4 January 2026|access-date=4 January 2026}}</ref> Three days later, a brace against [[Sunderland A.F.C.|Sunderland]] in a 3–0 victory for Brentford brought Thiago's season tally to 16 goals, making him the highest-scoring Brazilian player in a single Premier League season.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/en/news/4533742/brentford-forward-igor-thiago-sets-new-premier-league-goals-record-for-brazilian-players |title=Thiago sets record for goals from a Brazilian in a single season |publisher=Premier League |date=7 January 2026 }}</ref> When questioned by [[Jonathan Pearce (commentator)|Jonathan Pearce]], Brentford manager [[Keith Andrews (footballer)|Keith Andrews]] spoke about how Thiago has "earned his journey; he's had to graft" in his footballing career.<ref>{{cite episode |title="Match of the Day: 07/01/2026" |series=Match of the Day: 2025/26 |network=[[BBC]] |date=7 January 2026 |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/iplayer/episode/m002pl0j/match-of-the-day-202526-07012026}}</ref> On 11 April 2026, he scored twice in a 2–2 draw against Everton, taking his Premier League tally to 21 goals for the season and surpassing the club records previously held by [[Ivan Toney]] and [[Bryan Mbeumo]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.brentfordfc.com/en/news/article/analysis-brentford-2-everton-igor-thiago-premier-league |title=Analysis: Thiago's relentless goalscoring is rewriting Brentford history |publisher=Brentford F.C. |date=13 April 2026 }}</ref> He concluded the season with 22 goals, finishing second only to [[Erling Haaland]] in the scoring charts.<ref>{{cite web |last=Coverdale |first=David |url=https://www.premierleague.com/en/news/4668605/everything-thats-been-decided-in-202526-premier-league |title=EVERYTHING that's been decided in 2025/26 Premier League |publisher=Premier League |date=24 May 2026 }}</ref>

==International career==
Born in Brazil, Thiago received a [[Bulgarian passport]] in 2023, which made him available to play for [[Bulgaria national football team|Bulgaria]], subject to a five-year residency requirement, in addition to the [[Brazil national football team|Brazil national team]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=В Белгия: Тиаго може да е от изключителна полза за България |url=https://gong.bg/bg-football/nacionalen-tim/multimedia/video/v-belgiia-tiago-mozhe-da-e-ot-izkliuchitelna-polza-za-bylgariia-769631 |access-date=17 February 2024 |website=Gong.bg |language=bg}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |title=Гласят сензацията Игор Тиаго за национал на България |url=https://www.gol.bg/a/296-nacionalen-otbor/384197-glasyat-senzatsiyata-igor-tiago-za-natsional-na-balgariya |access-date=17 February 2024 |website=Gol |language=bg}}</ref> In January 2024 he received a call-up for [[Brazil national under-23 football team|Brazil U23]], but declined it reportedly to keep his international options open, despite the fact he said it would be a dream to represent Brazil on international level.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Игор Тиаго получи повиквателна от Бразилия и я отказа |url=https://gong.bg/football-sviat/drugi/multimedia/video/igor-tiago-poluchi-povikvatelna-ot-braziliia-i-ia-otkaza-772926 |access-date=17 February 2024 |website=Gong.bg |language=bg}}</ref>

On 16 March 2026, sitting as the Premier League's second-highest scorer behind only [[Erling Haaland]], Thiago earned his first call-up to the [[Brazil national football team|Brazil national team]] for friendlies against [[France national football team|France]] and [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2026-03-16 |title=Brazil: Brentford's Igor Thiago and Bournemouth's Rayan receive first call-ups |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/c8eg0y22w2ro |access-date=2026-03-17 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref>

